msgid ""
"This module is used to configure how the individual widgets are drawn by "
"&plasma;."
msgstr ""
"Selles moodulis saab määrata, millised näevad välja Plasmas kasutatavad "
"vidinad."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <emphasis>Widget</emphasis> is a commonly-used programmer's term for "
"referring to User Interface elements such as buttons, menus, and scroll "
"bars. You can think of them as the fundamental pieces that are assembled to "
"make your application."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Vidin</emphasis> on programmeerijate kõnepruugis sageli kasutatav "
"mõiste kasutajaliidese mitmesuguste osade, näiteks nuppude, menüüde ja "
"kerimisribade kohta. Neid võib võtta ka põhiosadena, millest rakendused "
"õigupoolest ongi kokku pandud."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure how the widgets are drawn with this module, but to change "
"the color of the widgets, you should refer to the section entitled <ulink "
"url=\"help:/kcontrol/colors/index.html\">Colors</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Siin saab määrata, kuidas vidinad välja näevad, kuid nende värvi muutmise "
"kohta loe lähemalt osa <ulink url=\"help:/kcontrol/colors/index.html"
"\">Värvid</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:43
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The top drop down box, labeled <guilabel>Widget Style</guilabel> contains "
#| "a list of the pre-defined styles. Each style has a name, and a brief "
#| "description."
msgid ""
"The top grid, labeled <guilabel>Application Style</guilabel> contains a list "
"of the previews of the pre-defined styles. Each style has a name, and a "
"brief description is shown when you hover its item with the mouse pointer."
msgstr ""
"Ülal asuvas rippmenüüs <guilabel>Vidina stiil</guilabel> on kirjas eelnevalt "
"määratud stiilid. Iga stiili juures on ära toodud selle nimi ja "
"lühikirjeldus."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to configure a &plasma; theme, use the <guilabel>Configure "
"Style...</guilabel> overlay icon at the bottom right of the widget style "
"icon in the grid."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If implemented, it is possible to change almost every aspect of the style: "
"center tabbar tabs, draw toolbar item separators, draw focus indicator in "
"lists, draw slider tick marks, enable extended resize handlers, define "
"keyboard accelerators visibility, windows' drag mode, use frames for the "
"better accessibility, use buttons on the scrollbars, use transparency in the "
"menus."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:53
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If a style is configurable, the <guibutton>Configure...</guibutton> "
#| "button at the right side of the drop down box is enabled and can be used "
#| "to open a dialog to select further settings."
msgid ""
"The general configuration can be made by pressing the <guibutton>Configure "
"Icons and Toolbars</guibutton> button below the grid. This button opens a "
"pane to select further settings."
msgstr ""
"Kui stiil on seadistatav, on rippmenüü paremas servas kasutatav nupp "
"<guibutton>Seadista...</guibutton>, millele klõpsates saab avada dialoogi, "
"kus saab asju täpsemalt seadistada."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:57
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Show icons on buttons"
msgid "Show icons: On buttons"
msgstr "Nuppudel näidatakse ikoone"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:59
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If this option is selected, action buttons (like <guibutton>OK</"
#| "guibutton> and <guibutton>Apply</guibutton>) will have a small icon "
#| "located within them to act as a visual reference. If this option is not "
#| "selected, then only text will appear on the button."
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, action buttons (like <guibutton>OK</guibutton> "
"and <guibutton>Apply</guibutton>) will have a small icon located within them "
"to act as a visual reference. If this option is not selected, then only text "
"will appear on the button."
msgstr ""
"Kui see on valitud, tekib toimingunuppudele (näiteks <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> ja <guibutton>Rakenda</guibutton>) väike ikoon, muutes nupud "
"visuaalselt atraktiivsemaks. Kui see on valimata, on nuppudel näha ainult "
"tekst."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:67
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Show icons in menus"
msgid "Show icons: In menus"
msgstr "Ikoonide näitamine menüüdes"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, &kde; applications will show small icons "
"alongside most menu items. If this option is not selected, then only text "
"will appear in the menus. Changes to the visibility of menu icons will only "
"affect newly started applications."
msgstr ""
"Selle valimisel näitavad &kde; rakendused enamiku menüükirjete kõrval "
"pisikesi ikoone. Kui see pole valitud, näeb menüüdes ainult teksti. "
"Menüüikoonide nägemise või mittenägemise muutmine avaldab mõju ainult pärast "
"muutmist käivitatud rakendustele."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:77
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<guilabel>Main toolbar text</guilabel>, <guilabel>Secondary toolbar text</"
#| "guilabel>"
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Main toolbar label</guilabel>, <guilabel>Secondary toolbar label</"
"guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Peamise tööriistariba tekst</guilabel>, <guilabel>Teisese "
"tööriistariba tekst</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "These drop down boxes lets you determine where on the button in both "
#| "toolbars the text name of the button will appear as the default. If "
#| "<guilabel>No Text</guilabel> is selected, then there is no text on the "
#| "toolbar buttons. If <guilabel>Text Only</guilabel> is selected, then the "
#| "button's icon is replaced with a text name of the button. If "
#| "<guilabel>Text Beside Icons</guilabel> is selected, then the name of the "
#| "button will be placed to the <emphasis>right</emphasis> of the icon. If "
#| "<guilabel>Text Below Icons</guilabel> is selected, the default will be to "
#| "have the text of the button <emphasis>below</emphasis> the icon."
msgid ""
"These drop down boxes let you determine where on the button in both toolbars "
"the text name of the button will appear as the default. If <guilabel>None</"
"guilabel> is selected, then there is no text on the toolbar buttons. If "
"<guilabel>Text only</guilabel> is selected, then the button's icon is "
"replaced with a text name of the button. If <guilabel>Beside icons</"
"guilabel> is selected, then the name of the button will be placed to the "
"<emphasis>right</emphasis> of the icon. If <guilabel>Below icon</guilabel> "
"is selected, the default will be to have the text of the button "
"<emphasis>below</emphasis> the icon."
msgstr ""
"Rippmenüüdega saab määrata, kuhu ilmub mõlema tööriistariba nuppudel "
"vaikimisi selle nimetus. Kui valitud on <guilabel>Tekst puudub</guilabel>, "
"puudub tööriistariba nuppudel tekst. Kui valitud on <guilabel>Ainult tekst</"
"guilabel>, asendatakse nupuikoonid nupu nimetusega. Kui valitud on "
"<guilabel>Tekst ikoonide kõrval</guilabel>, näidatakse nupu nimetust "
"ikoonist <emphasis>paremal pool</emphasis>. Kui valitud on <guilabel>Tekst "
"ikoonide all</guilabel>, seisab nupu nimetus vaikimisi ikooni <emphasis>all</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This option only specifies the <emphasis>default</emphasis> location. "
#| "Each application can override the setting used in this panel."
msgid ""
"These options only specify the <emphasis>default</emphasis> location. Each "
"application can override the settings used in this panel."
msgstr ""
"See võimalus kehtib ainult <emphasis>vaikimisi</emphasis>. Iga rakendus võib "
"oma seadistustega sellel paneelil määratu tühistada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guibutton>Configure GNOME/GTK Application Style...</guibutton> button "
"can be used to open the configuration tab where you can choose <guilabel>GTK "
"theme</guilabel>, install GTK theme from file or <guibutton>Get New GNOME/"
"GTK Application Styles</guibutton> from the Internet."
msgstr ""

